    <title>_chdrive </title>
    <volume>C Run-Time Library</volume>
    <routine_idx> dir_idx.htm </routine_idx>

    <description>
        <para>Changes the current working drive</para>
    </description>

    <syntax>
        <return_val>int</return_val>
        <func_name>_chdrive</func_name>
        <parameters>
            <func_param>
                <param_type>int</param_type>
                <param_name>drive</param_name>
                <param_note>
                <para>Number of the new working drive.</para>
                </param_note>
            </func_param>
        </parameters>
    </syntax>
  
    <return>
        <para>_chdrive returns a value of 0 if the working drive is successfully changed. A return value of ¨C1 indicates an error.</para>
    </return>
    <remark>
    <para>The _chdrive function changes the current working drive to the drive specified by drive</para>
    <para>The drive parameter uses an integer to specify the new working drive (1=A, 2=B, and so forth).This function changes only the working drive; _chdir changes the working directory.This function changes only the working drive; _chdir changes the working directory.This function changes only the working drive; _chdir changes the working directory.</para>
    </remark>
